type: web_research
title: Interactive VSL Image Pacing & Video Optimization Research
key_insights[12]: "Interactive video branching: 90% completion rate (Wirewax data), vs 23.7% average YouTube retention","Cognitive load: Segmented videos outperform whole videos; breaks between segments reduce extraneous load","ASL benchmarks: Action=2-4.5sec/shot, Drama=4-6sec, Slow-burn=up to 30sec, Modern film average=4-6sec","Ken Burns effect: 15-20% higher completion rates vs static images, 45% better engagement in social feeds","Testimonial optimal: 60-90 seconds per testimonial, under 2 minutes max","CTA: Average 16% conversion rate (Wistia), repeat every 3-4 minutes, max 2-3 CTAs per video","AI video backfire: Uncanny valley erodes trust, consumers label AI video as 'slop', distrust synthetic endorsements","Japan presentation pace: 1 slide/1 min for webinar, 1 slide/2-3 min for general presentation","Japan VSL market: Ishizaki Rikiya 22-step template dominant, AI-assisted script generation trending","I2V 2026: Runway Gen-4.5 #1 quality, Kling 2.0 longest duration (2min), fal.ai cheapest API access","Video vs image: Live-action best for tangible products/testimonials, animation for abstract concepts","Decision point pacing: Slow down before choices (reduce cognitive load), provide processing time"
findings[7]: "Interactive video re-engagement: branching gives viewers control, increases time spent exploring outcomes",55% of viewers lost by 60-second mark in standard video - interactive branching significantly improves this,First 8-15 seconds critical for VSL hook - unexpected image + intriguing statement,"Fear/urgency scenes: FOMO drives faster decision-making, use scarcity + urgency combo","Japan LINE platform: 97M users, 80%+ reach, video ads effective across all age groups",Kling O1 claims 247% improvement over Veo 3.1 for image reference tasks,"Wirewax tracks 150+ data points per video, real-time analytics dashboard"
recommendations[9]: Use 8-12 images/min for high-tension fear scenes (2-4.5 sec ASL),Use 3-4 images/min for testimonial scenes (15-20 sec per image),Use 4-6 images/min for educational/concept scenes (10-15 sec per image),Use 2-3 focused images for CTA scenes with 5-8 sec display each,Slow pacing 50% before branch points to reduce cognitive load,"Use Ken Burns for 80%+ of scenes, reserve real video for key emotional moments only",Avoid AI-generated video for human faces/testimonials (uncanny valley risk),"Use I2V (Runway/Kling) only for nature, abstract, and non-human scenes","For Japan 30-50 male audience: slightly slower pace than Western VSL, more data-driven visuals"
